inheritance in css is applied from parent element to child element

some properties will be inherited from the parent element and will be applied to 
    child element if the child element doesn't override the property

****************************************
html:
<body>
    <p>test</p>
</body>

css:
body {
  font-family: sans-serif; -> this will be applied (as long as it doesn't get overriden)
  color: #444;
}

p{
    color: red; -> this will be applied (override the parent's property)
}
****************************************

the universal selector (*) select every single element on the page
